product.longDescription: A peroxide-based treatment for the prevention and control of plant pathogens in field-grown crops and commercial greenhouses. Broadly labeled for use as a pre-plant dip, soil drench, foliar treatment, and surface disinfectant. Alternate use with copper fungicide helps prevent development of tolerant strains of bacteria and fungi. Typical usage is 1/3-1 gal/acre. Ground shipments only.
